<HL>
   International Brief -- Lonrho PLC:
   British Overseas Trader Buys
   10% Stake in German Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
07/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   G.ASK U.LRH G.MAS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lonrho PLC, a British overseas trader, said it purchased a
10% stake in Asko Deutsche Kaufhaus AG, a German wholesale
and retail store operator, for 94 million pounds ($170.7
million).
   Tiny Rowland, Lonrho's chairman, will join Asko's
supervisory board. The Asko stake "will enable Lonrho to make
further advances in the expanding opportunities which will
occur" in Germany as well as Eastern Europe, the company
said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Lonrho is buying the holding from German retailer Massa
AG. The stake will be paid for by a mixture of 8.5 million
Lonrho shares and the balance of 71 million pounds in cash.
</TEXT>
